Hillhouse Capital Group (“Hillhouse”) is an investment management firm founded by Zhang Lei in 2005 with US$20 million[1] in seed capital from the Yale Endowment.[2]
Hillhouse manages over US$20 billion as of January 2016[citation needed] and is known for its avoidance of publicity.[3][4] Hillhouse manages capital for institutional clients such as university endowments, foundations, sovereign wealth funds, pension funds and family offices. Hillhouse is a long-term fundamental research-driven equity investor. Hillhouse focuses on the consumer, TMT, industrials and healthcare sectors and invests in companies across all equity stages.[5]
Hillhouse has over 30 investment professionals across its offices in Beijing, Hong Kong and Singapore. It invests globally, with a particular focus on Asia.



